The four police officers accused of murder in the shooting death of Amadou Diallo plan to testify in their own defense at their trial next month and are leaning toward choosing a trial by a judge instead of a jury, according to their lawyers.
The testimony of the officers, and its credibility, will be focal points of the trial because there were no other witnesses to the initial encounter in February between Diallo, a West African immigrant, and the plainclothes officers who killed him in a fusillade of 41 bullets.
